<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-13T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-13T06:00:00-05:00" n="8" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d8">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">641.5531/19: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador to the Belgian Government in Exile</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-13T13:00:00+02:00">May 13,
                                    1942—1 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received May 13—8:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Belgian Series No. 8. My 3, April 30, 10 p.m. Vleeschauwer now plans to
                            leave for Congo via United States on May 15. He feels he cannot longer
                            postpone departure since this would dislocate his entire program.</p>
                        <p>Joseph Jennen, Economic Adviser to Colonial Ministry, however has been
                            given full power to negotiate the United States-United Kingdom-Belgian
                            Congo agreement.</p>
                        <closer>[<signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Biddle</hi>
                            </signed>]</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>